Limpopo and KwaZulu-Natal are among those who still celebrate the day of love.South Africans in the Western Cape may celebrate a lot of things, however, Valentine s Day does not seem to be one of them. According a survey done by OnlineCasting, the day, meant to be celebrated by lovers, is becoming less popular. The study has revealed that Google Trends has showed that online searches about Valentine s Day have been on the decline since 2006.Northern Cape was found to be the province that celebrates the day of love the most, followed by the Free State, KwaZulu-Natal, Limpopo and Eastern Cape. Gauteng, Mpumalanga and North West were also at the bottom of the list, reports Daily Sun.On the contrary, Mother s Day was found to be growing in popularity since 2007, compared to Father s Day that has not increased in popularity since 2010. Source: www.onlinecasting.co.za 